==========================================================================
Toward a Theory of Multilevel Evolution: Long-Term Information Integration Shapes the Mutational Landscape and Enhances Evolvability
- discusses increased evolvability separte from population diversity
   "However, the increase of evolvability is essentially different from the 
   increase in population variability due to an increase of neutrality. In
   the examples discussed here, evolution actually increases (the effect of)
   mutational changes “in the right direction."
  (http://www-binf.bio.uu.nl/BINF/theoryMLE.pdf)

==========================================================================
Evolution of Evolvability in Gene Regulatory Networks
Crombach and Hogeweg
https://journals.plos.org/ploscompbiol/article?id=10.1371/journal.pcbi.1000112
- environment changes over time
- complex gene regulatory networks
- "We show that the population evolves towards genotype-phenotype mappings that
  allow for an orchestrated network-wide change in the gene expression pattern,
  requiring only a few specific gene indels. The genes involved are hubs of the
  networks"

