Feed-Forward Loop Circuits as a Side Effect of Genome Evolution
- Interesting link between certain structures and molecular biology:
  feed-forward loop circuits- top-level node A conntected to B which is in turn
  connected to C,D,E,F, but A is also directly connected to each of C,D,E,F.
  Do we see anything like this?
  (https://academic.oup.com/mbe/article/23/10/1931/1096976)

